-- Jets Fall 26-17 to Lions in Preseason Game, Geno Smith Injured
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-08-10T04:31:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-10/jets-fall-26-17-to-lions-in-preseason-game-geno-smith-injured.html
The  New York  Jets lost 26-17 to the
 Detroit Lions  as quarterback  Mark Sanchez  gave up a touchdown on
an interception and his main competitor for the starting
position, Geno Smith, was hurt.  Ezekiel Ansah returned a Sanchez interception 14 yards for
a touchdown early in the first quarter at Ford Field in Detroit.
After a David Akers field goal put the Lions ahead 10-0, Sanchez
hit Jeff Cumberland with a 26-yard pass for a score.  Sanchez left the game after completing 10 of 13 passes for
125 yards in both teamsâ€™ opening National Football League
preseason game of 2013.  Smith, a rookie from West Virginia, left early in the third
quarter with a right ankle injury. During his appearance, he
completed six of seven passes for 47 yards.  To contact the reporter on this story:
